description.narrative: By 2025, Communication and community platforms strengthened to increase and sustain demand for high-quality MNCAH services and the adoption of positive health practices especially for vulnerable population, which contributes to Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence, Immunization Services As Part Of Primary Health Care, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being, Nutrition Of Adolescents And Women, Strengthening Primary Health Care And High-Impact Health Interventions, Strengthening Primary Health Care And High-Impact Health Interventions (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Partnerships And Engagement: Public And Private, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: 'By 2025, newborns, children, adolescent girls and women benefit from an equitable, high-quality and resilient health system across the continuum of care

description.narrative: High (81%) acceptance of COVID-19 vaccinations among the community members was recorded after UNICEF support towards development and implementation of demand promotion strategies on such vaccinations. The developed materials reached targets withCOVID-19 vaccine messages. As a result,8,716,959million people are vaccinated. Furthermore, over 60 million people were reached with COVID-19 risk communication and community engagement (RCCE) interventions through different communication platforms, such as social media, SMS, hotlines and print and audio-visual media. UNICEF also took the lead on development of national C4D strategies on nOPV2 introduction campaign and Oral Cholera Vaccination campaign. | Status:Met | As-of Date:07/01/2022
